      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(anthropic): send current claude-cli user-agent on OAuth path",
        "body": "Closes #94716\n\n## What Problem This Solves\nUsers authenticating to Anthropic via the `claude-cli` OAuth backend (`anthropic/claude-*` with `sk-ant-oat...` token) got `authentication_error: Invalid bearer token` even though the token worked in standalone `claude` CLI. The OAuth path sent a hardcoded `user-agent: claude-cli/2.1.75` (April 2025), which Anthropic's recency window rejected.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\nCollapse two independent hardcoded version sites into a single source of truth (`claude-code-user-agent.ts`). Bump default to `2.1.177` (reporter-confirmed working) and add `OPENCLAW_CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION` override for future bumps. Deliberately avoids shelling out to `claude --version` — that runs on the hot auth path and assumes standalone CLI is installed.\n\n## User Impact\nOAuth (`sk-ant-oat...`) requests to Anthropic stop failing with `Invalid bearer token`. If Anthropic tightens the window again, operators set `OPENCLAW_CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION=<semver>` and recover immediately.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Before (negative control — stale `claude-cli/2.1.75`):**\n```\nstale user-agent (OAuth path):          claude-cli/2.1.75\nstill sends stale claude-cli/2.1.75?   true\nBUG CONFIRMED: OAuth path sends claude-cli/2.1.75 which Anthropic rejects\n```\n\n**After (fix applied):**\n```\n$ node --import tsx scripts/proof-anthropic-oauth-user-agent.mts\ndefault user-agent (OAuth path):          claude-cli/2.1.177\nstill sends stale claude-cli/2.1.75?       false\nOPENCLAW_CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION=2.1.250 user-agent:  claude-cli/2.1.250\nPROOF PASS\n```\n\n**Vitest:**\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/llm/providers/claude-code-user-agent.test.ts src/llm/providers/anthropic.test.ts src/agents/anthropic-transport-stream.test.ts --run\n Test Files  3 passed (3) / Tests  120 passed (120)\n```",
        "branch": "fix/anthropic-oauth-user-agent-version",
